parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Fire due to Brake Master Cylinder Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause an electrical fire, leading to a total loss of the vehicle, damage to surrounding property, and potential harm to individuals.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire while parked
with flames originating from the engine compartment
often on the driver's side. The fire may start suddenly
without warning
and can spread quickly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer can cause the driver to be unable to accurately determine their speed, which can lead to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: The speedometer becomes inoperable
with no warning lights illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake fluid pressure sensor can cause the brake tail lights to fail intermittently, leading to potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake fluid pressure sensor leaks onto the electrical main computer wires
causing the brake tail lights to fail intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dual fuel tank system can cause fuel to leak or overflow from the tanks, resulting in a fire hazard, environmental damage, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leaks or spills from the fuel tank cap
fuel tank overflows
fuel pressure builds up in the tank
fuel gauge malfunctions
fuel transfers from one tank to another
and fuel spills onto the ground.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or will not start
fuel pressure regulator needs to be replaced
fuel pump failure
and fuel leaks from the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the fuel tank straps can cause the fuel tank to detach from the vehicle, resulting in fuel leaks and potential accidents.
symptoms: Fuel tank straps are corroded
fuel tank detaches from the vehicle
and fuel leaks from the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Brake fluid leakage
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
vehicle is unable to stop
burning smell or overheating of brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the brake lines can cause brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Brake fluid leakage
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
vehicle is unable to stop
corrosion on brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunction of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to skid or lose control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle pulls to one side when brakes are applied
ABS light comes on
vibration or pulsation when brakes are applied
loud squealing noise when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A short circuit in the cruise control system can cause a fire, leading to damage or injury.
symptoms: Smoke or flames from under the hood
burning smell
cruise control switch malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of brake pads and rotors can cause brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Squealing noise when brakes are applied
vibration or pulsation when brakes are applied
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.
